00:34:34.090 --> 00:34:41.770
So look, Google's a fine stock. I'm not saying
you shouldn't own Google, but you don't want

00:34:41.770 --> 00:34:44.179
everything in Google.

00:34:44.179 --> 00:34:50.890
And you don't want everything in the United
States. What we know about investing is that

00:34:50.890 --> 00:34:59.060
people have a home country bias, they have
much too much of their money in their home

00:34:59.060 --> 00:35:00.060
country.

00:35:00.060 --> 00:35:07.410
For example, in France institutional, France
is 3% of the world's GDP. Institutional investors

00:35:07.410 --> 00:35:13.581
in France have 97% of their holdings in French
securities. That's what we call the home country

00:35:13.581 --> 00:35:14.581
bias.

00:35:14.581 --> 00:35:21.080
The U.S. is only 40% of the world economy.
The emerging markets are growing much faster

00:35:21.080 --> 00:35:23.730
than the developed markets.

00:35:23.730 --> 00:35:30.090
I know that the word "China" is a dirty word
around here --

00:35:30.090 --> 00:35:31.090
[laughter]

00:35:31.090 --> 00:35:38.020
but the growth of China has been absolutely
unprecedented. China has grown after inflation

00:35:38.020 --> 00:35:44.110
over the last 20 years at growth rates between
9 and 10%.

00:35:44.110 --> 00:35:51.800
China has surpassed Japan this year as the
world's second largest economy and the Chinese

00:35:51.800 --> 00:36:00.030
Yuan or RMB is a severely undervalued currency.
So, I wanna argue for much more diversification.

00:36:00.030 --> 00:36:10.200
China's a very interesting story. China in
the early 1800's had about a third of the

00:36:10.200 --> 00:36:17.340
world's GDP and then all hell broke loose.
They were beaten in two opium wars by the

00:36:17.340 --> 00:36:25.850
British. They were invaded by Japan, in the
1900's. Japan wasn't thrown out 'till 1945.

00:36:25.850 --> 00:36:28.180
There was a damaging civil war.

00:36:28.180 --> 00:36:34.940
Then Mao came in and the end of the Mao years
was a so-called cultural revolution where

00:36:34.940 --> 00:36:41.190
the universities were closed. Anybody with
any knowledge was sent out to the countryside

00:36:41.190 --> 00:36:50.130
to be reeducated and you ended up in 1980
with China maybe between 3and 4% of the world's

00:36:50.130 --> 00:36:51.130
GDP.

00:36:51.130 --> 00:36:56.700
And then this remarkable man Deng Xiaopingcame
in who was everything that Mao wasn't. Mao

00:36:56.700 --> 00:37:05.550
was an ideologue. Deng Xiaoping was an intensely
practical person. He would say, "I don't care

00:37:05.550 --> 00:37:13.820
if the cat is black or white just as long
it catches mice. To be rich is glorious. I

00:37:13.820 --> 00:37:18.030
don't know whether stock markets are good
or bad, but let's try them."

00:37:18.030 --> 00:37:27.590
And you ushered in this remarkable era of
30 years of unprecedented growth. China's

00:37:27.590 --> 00:37:34.610
never grown; no country in history has grown
as fast as China. China is probably 12% of

00:37:34.610 --> 00:37:43.300
the world's GDP now and according to IMF estimates
will be between 15 and 20%of the world's GDP

00:37:43.300 --> 00:37:45.800
by 2014.

00:37:45.800 --> 00:37:51.010
Now one of the things that the reason I think
China will grow is all the growth thus far

00:37:51.010 --> 00:37:59.120
has been in the Eastern part of the country.
The center and West are still dirt poor and

00:37:59.120 --> 00:38:04.780
people are restless there. There's a lot of
unrest in this area. The government wants

00:38:04.780 --> 00:38:10.600
to stay in power and so government policy
is, "We've got to keep this growth machine

00:38:10.600 --> 00:38:11.950
going."

00:38:11.950 --> 00:38:19.390
And China had a fiscal stimulus program. They
were the first to get out of the worldwide

00:38:19.390 --> 00:38:22.330
recession. They had a fiscal stimulus that
was much bigger than ours relative to GDP

00:38:22.330 --> 00:38:25.320
and they've got the wherewithal to do it.

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:31.480
We now have a deb- to-GDP ratio in the United
States that's getting close to a 100%. Europe's

00:38:31.480 --> 00:38:38.040
is close to a 100%. We know what's happening
in Greece right now because people are worried

00:38:38.040 --> 00:38:47.450
about buying Greek debt. Japan's is over 200%
of the world's GDP; debt-to-GDP is over 200%;

00:38:47.450 --> 00:38:56.300
China's is 20%. So, they've got a very strong
fiscal balance and tremendous human capital.

00:38:56.300 --> 00:39:02.600
The Chinese have revered education since the
time of Confucius. They are hard working.

00:39:02.600 --> 00:39:07.550
They're entrepreneurial. They have a gambling
spirit which is I think anybody's who's gonna

00:39:07.550 --> 00:39:17.000
be an entrepreneur has to be a bit of a gambler.
It is a growth story that I am sure will continue.

